<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1234,2042]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1304,1330]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,886,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiformis" status="new species" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[329,513,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Indoceoplanetes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[529,712,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Indoceoplanetes</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[730,886,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ephippiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[893,1031,1304,1331]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[893,1031,1304,1331]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is not morphologically close to any other species in the subgenus, and can be separated from all other known species of 
<emphasis box="[1116,1147,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">In.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2017" box="[1164,1347,1340,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1164,1347,1340,1366]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Indoceoplanetes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the following characters: male tergopleurite IV–VI each with 1 
<emphasis box="[818,840,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ss</emphasis>
on each side and tergopleurites VII–VIII with 2 
<emphasis box="[1380,1402,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ss</emphasis>
on each side (
<figureCitation box="[272,358,1411,1438]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–58" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[244,1338,203,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-23@26.[230,1358,181,1921]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 57–58. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 57, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 58, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825585/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
); shape of proximal mesosome (
<figureCitation box="[727,811,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
); large, hook-shaped antero-lateral extensions of gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[217,300,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
); medianly bulging distal margin of mesosome (
<figureCitation box="[846,929,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
); proportionately broad and bulky parameres (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1482,1508]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1234,2042]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,480,1517,1544]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,473,1517,1544]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head rounded trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[787,870,1517,1544]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head convex, frons slightly concave. Marginal carina broad, narrowing anterior to 
<emphasis box="[877,933,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">dsms</emphasis>
, deeply displaced and widened at osculum. Ventral anterior plate rounded triangular, with concave anterior margin. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[1211,1293,1588,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi wide, bulging. Pre- and post-ocular nodi large, connected dorsally by broad ocular band. Marginal temporal carina slender. Gular plate triangular, lateral margins concave. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[1304,1433,1659,1686]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–58" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[244,1338,203,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-23@26.[230,1358,181,1921]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 57–58. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 57, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 58, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825585/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs 57–58</figureCitation>
. Base pigmentation translucent; preantennal and preocular nodi dark brown; area delimited by dotted line in 
<figureCitation box="[1350,1431,1695,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
, gular plate, proepimera, and metepisterna medium brown; sternal plates III–VI and subgenital plates pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1234,2042]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,1765,1792]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[747,831,1766,1793]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–58" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[244,1338,203,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-23@26.[230,1358,181,1921]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 57–58. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 57, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 58, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825585/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
; tergopleurite IV–VI each with 1 
<emphasis box="[1216,1238,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ss</emphasis>
on each side and tergopleurites VII–VIII with 2 
<emphasis box="[492,514,1802,1827]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ss</emphasis>
on each side. Basal apodeme rounded rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1162,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
), lateral margins slightly concave. Proximal mesosome with oblique, bluntly rounded antero-lateral extensions (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1224,1837,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
), proximal margin concave. Mesosomal lobes divergent distally. Distal margin of mesosome concave laterally but bulging medianly. Gonopore shaped as in 
<figureCitation box="[412,493,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–63" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[187,1390,197,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[178,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 59–63. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) ephippiformis new species ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 59, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 60, male genitalia, dorsal view. 61, male mesosome, ventral view. 62, male paramere, dorsal view. 63, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825587/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
, with large hook-shaped antero-lateral extensions. Dorsal fringe small, tilted slightly distally, without thumb-like process. Chaetotaxy: 2 ventral 
<emphasis box="[832,904,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">gpmes</emphasis>
microsetae on each side of distal gonopore; 2 
<emphasis box="[151,216,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">lpmes</emphasis>
sensilla on each side on mesosomal lobes; 1 dorsal 
<emphasis box="[798,856,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ames</emphasis>
microseta on each side distal to dorsal fringe. Parameres and 
<emphasis box="[272,347,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
