<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from “ 
<emphasis box="[754,866,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ephippion</emphasis>
”, Greek for “saddle”, and the ending “ 
<emphasis box="[1303,1384,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">-formis</emphasis>
” for “having the shape of”, referring to the shape of the proximal mesosome.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
